The paper discusses game theory and human behavior in social dilemmas, which are topics commonly studied in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of translucent players also involves modeling and reasoning about beliefs and perceptions, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social intelligence (cs.SI). The paper also touches on decision-making and optimization, which are relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
